<p class="rm-manual">Â© Getty</p>
<p>Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer (D) on Sunday said she exempted 
religious services from a statewide ban on gatherings of 50 or more 
people amid the coronavirus outbreak at the behest of the Republican 
legislature but said she strongly discouraged such gatherings.</p>
<p>âWeâre discouraging people from gathering at all,â Whitmer said on âFox News Sunday.â </p>
<p>âThatâs an area we donât have the ability to directly enforce and 
control,â she added, citing the separation of church and state.</p>
<p>Guest host John Roberts asked Whitmer about the "Big Three" 
automakers shuttering amid the pandemic and whether the auto industry 
requires federal funds.</p>
<p>âI applaud the big three working with the UAW [United Autoworkers] in
 making that decision but at the end of the day weâve got to make sure 
we can still be competitive,â Whitmer responded.</p>
<p>Roberts also asked Whitmer about attacks on her by <span><a href="file:///people/donald-trump">President Trump</a><span><span><span><a href="file:///people/donald-trump">Donald John Trump</a><a href="file:///policy/energy-environment/502402-senate-advances-public-lands-bill-in-late-night-vote">Senate advances public lands bill in late-night vote</a> <a href="file:///homenews/senate/502405-warren-dems-urge-trump-to-back-down-from-veto-threat-over-changing">Warren, Democrats urge Trump to back down from veto threat over changing Confederate-named bases</a> <a href="file:///policy/defense/502404-esper-orders-after-action-review-of-national-guards-role-in-protests">Esper orders 'After Action Review' of National Guard's role in protests</a> <a href="file:///people/donald-trump">MORE</a></span></span></span></span>, who referred to her as âfailing Michigan governorâ on Twitter last week.</p>
<p>âI think the irony of the attack on Twitter is weâve already been 
much more aggressive than the federal government,â Whitmer responded. 
âWe have to have truth in communication, we have to be making decisions 
based on science and facts. We canât have half-truths and hyperbole â¦ 
convincing people this isnât to be taken seriously.â</p>
